Test Cases for Fakestagram:

Note: For all necessary test cases, the User that can be used will have the following information:
User 1:
Email Address: test@test.com
		Password: testtest
User 2:
Email Address: test2@test.com
		Password: test2test2


1.	Test login with correct user fields
•	Acting as a User, 
•	Visit the Login page
•	Fill in all the input fields with the same details as initialised by the User
•	Click on the login button
•	Assert true if it redirects you to the home page

2.	Test login with incorrect user fields
•	Acting as a User, 
•	Visit the Login page
•	Fill in all the input fields with a different password/username as initialised by the User
•	Click on the login button
•	Assert true if it redirects you back to the login page with an error

3.	Test registration
•	Visit the Register page
•	Fill in the user fields with a valid Email address and Password
•	Click on the register button
•	Assert true if it redirects you to the home page

4.	Check if you can follow a user
•	Acting as a User,
•	After logging in, visit the homepage
•	Click on the follow button
•	Assert true if database updates and now shows you following that user

5.	Test Posting an image with a caption
•	Acting as a User,
•	Visit the home page
•	Click on “upload an Image”
•	Pick a random sample image to be uploaded
•	Add a sample string in the caption text box
•	Click on upload
•	Assert true if you are redirected to the home page
•	Assert true if image is uploaded successfully with the caption

6.	Test being able to comment
•	Acting as a User,
•	Visit the home page
•	Click on the text box underneath the posted picture
•	Input a string of text
•	Post that comment 
•	Assert true if the comment is visible after posting
•	Assert true if Database now shows that comment in it

7.	Test if posted image is visible to another user
•	Acting as a User,
•	Visit the home page 
•	Post a sample Image with/without a caption
•	Logout
•	Acting as a different User
•	Visit the home page
•	Check if any images as shown on the homepage
•	Assert true if the sample image is displayed

8.	Test if “Following Users” is updated when you follow a new user
•	Acting as a User
•	Visit the home page 
•	Post an image with/without a caption
•	Now, acting as a different user,
•	Visit the home page
•	Click on the “follow” button next to User name of the person who posted the image
•	Visit the User Page
•	Check if the Following tab now displays the name of the first user 
•	Assert true if name is found

9.	Test if User Pages displays all images posted by the user 
•	Acting as a user,
•	Visit the home page
•	Post 3 sample images, with/without a caption
•	Visit the User page
•	 Assert true if all 3 images are displayed 

10.	Test if “Follow” button updates to “Following” If clicked on
•	Acting as a User,
•	Visit the home page
•	Click on the “Follow” button next to User name of the person who posted the image
•	Check if it updates to “Following”
•	Assert true if it does



	
